21 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative intent.
22 The General Assembly finds that:
23 (1) The services provided by freight railroads are essential to
24 the functionality of the state;
25 (2) It is the obligation of the General Assembly to protect rail
26 employees who are involved in accidents or incidents; and
27 (3) The requirements of this act are intended to eliminate, when
28 possible, undue harassment or assault of rail crew members involved in
29 railroad fatalities.
